<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4928520>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 25–27. cf. Parahistricostoma tuberculatum (C. L. Koch & Berendt, 1854), juvenile, SIZK UA-1565, from Rovno amber (precise locality unclear), Ukraine; late Eocene. 25 Dorso-lateral overview of the complete animal. 26 Detail of 25, showing anterior prosoma and pedipalps with clavate setae (arrowed), dorso-lateral view. 27 Detail of 26 close up showing palpal segments with clavate setae; note also the head of clavate seta (arrowed), lateral view. Scale bars: 25: 1 mm; 26: 0.2 mm; 27: 0.05 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4928520/files/figure.png" .

